  🔧 Root Cause

  The November 10, 2025 QueryBuilder decomposition split the monolithic service into 5 sub-services, but QueryValidator wasn't updated to work with the new architecture. It was trying to call:
  - self.parser.parse_query() ❌ (parser doesn't exist)
  - self.build_optimized_query() ❌ (moved to QueryOptimizer)
  - self.from_template() ❌ (moved to QueryTemplateManager)

  ✨ Solution: Dependency Injection Pattern

  1. Updated QueryValidator to accept dependencies:
  class QueryValidator:
      def __init__(
          self,
          schema_service,
          optimizer: "QueryOptimizer | None" = None,          # ← Injected
          template_manager: "QueryTemplateManager | None" = None,  # ← Injected
      ):
          self.optimizer = optimizer
          self.template_manager = template_manager

  2. Fixed all method delegations:
  - ✅ validate_and_optimize() → delegates to optimizer.build_optimized_query()
  - ✅ build_from_natural_language() → delegates to template_manager.from_template()
  - ✅ Query parsing → uses analyze_query_intent() function

  3. Updated QueryBuilder facade to wire dependencies:
  self.optimizer = QueryOptimizer(schema_service)
  self.templates = QueryTemplateManager(schema_service)
  self.validator = QueryValidator(
      schema_service,
      optimizer=self.optimizer,          # ← Wired
      template_manager=self.templates,   # ← Wired
  )

  📝 Files Modified

